-- Fiat Group's Car Sales in Italy Dropped 35% in July, la Repubblica Reports
-- Tommaso Ebhardt
-- 2010-08-02T06:32:24Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-08-02/fiat-group-s-car-sales-in-italy-dropped-35-in-july-la-repubblica-reports.html

          
          
             Fiat SpA’s sales in Italy dropped 35
percent in July, la Repubblica reported on its website citing
Filippo Pavan Bernacchi, head of the Italian dealer association
Federauto.  
 Italian car registrations fell 26 percent in July, Pavan
told the Italian daily. Federauto asked Berlusconi’s government
for new incentives to boost the market, la Repubblica said.  
          
          


  


        